HEADWORD: Gadwall
<hw>Gad"wall</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Gad</ets> to
walk about + <ets>well</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large
duck (<spn>Anas strepera</spn>), valued as a game bird, found in the
northern parts of Europe and America; -- called also <altname>gray
duck</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>gaddwell</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gaea</ent>⟦br⟧
